snippet.title: San Francisco tech shuttle pilot program clears road block appeal
snippet.description: The controversial "Google bus" pilot program will go ahead without the environmental review opponents appealed for, but now the tech industry backlash undercurrents at play may only intensify.

snippet.title: Airbnb to collect hotel taxes in San Francisco
snippet.description: Starting this summer, the online vacation rental service plans to collect and remit taxes on behalf of hosts.

snippet.title: 2013 Hyundai Veloster Turbo review
snippet.description: The 2013 Hyundai Veloster Turbo adds a healthy dose of straight-line performance to its techie, trendy formula.

snippet.title: Google wants to dock mystery barge in San Francisco
snippet.description: No authorization has been granted, but the tech giant talked with the National Park Service about towing the mystery structure, which seems related to Google Glass, into San Francisco's Fort Mason.

snippet.title: When the Bay Bridge towered over San Francisco
snippet.description: A new exhibit at San Francisco's de Young museum showcases photographs and art of the construction of the Bay Bridge in the mid- to late '30s.

snippet.title: San Francisco Airport uses tech to meet runway safety standards
snippet.description: In order to meet a federal directive, the airport will close two runways this summer to install a special concrete material that will bring runaway aircraft quickly to a stop.

snippet.title: New San Francisco Apple Store gets final approval
snippet.description: The San Francisco Board of Supervisors gave the go-ahead for Apple to build a new flagship store in the city's Union Square district.

snippet.title: LG Lucid 2 (Verizon Wireless) review
snippet.description: Though it has a few minor flaws, the reliable performance and rock-bottom price of Verizon's Lucid 2 will satisfy first-time smartphone users on a budget.
